reviews.title: Unfassbar schlecht
reviews.text:
I order on the bar and explain very deeply, that I am allergic against Lactose, So please do my Burger without cheese.
Waiting 30 minutes Burger is coming with a lot of cheese..
Believe me, I was angry, more like angry.
WHY is it not possible, to be present for the guests, listen to the guest and present him a nice stay. Here we get a dirty, old rooms, which are from the 70 thies, the Ceiling was getting water and ist complete damage, the shower is molded with fungus, short, this is not a 4 Star Bestwestern this is a old dirty hotels, which get to much bus tourists.
When this tourist are finished with the breakfast then for the normally guest  is not so much available.
On last day I asked for 2 fried eggs, Answer was short and precise: NO!!! Realy.

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!

tripContent.title: Santa Fe: heritage & history on the Original Route 66
tripContent.description: Looking for adventure on the original Route 66? Santa Fe, the oldest state capital, is a must-stop for history buffs. The city, founded in 1610, is older than the United States—but the area has been populated for well over a thousand years. With so much history and heritage, you'll want to allow plenty of time to explore the best of the Southwest—so here are 12 suggestions for things to see, do, and learn.

articleContent.title: How to visit Chicxulub crater—the dinosaur-ending asteroid site in Mexico

seoInfo.metaDescription: Scientists speculate that Chicxulub crater was the asteroid-impact site that killed the dinosaurs—and it's just a day’s road trip from Cancun. It’s still possible to see evidence of the impact with your own eyes—if you know where to look.

reviews.title: Super gutes Essen!
reviews.text:
Erstmal finde ich es gut, dass sie Umweltfreundliche Mayonaise-Behälter haben.
Zudem hatten wir (3 Pers.) alle den „MRIJ Beefburger“ und er schmeckte fantastisch, wir haben ihn Medium bestellt. Das Essen und die Getränke kamen schnell.

Insgesamt war der Aufenthalt SUPER!

reviews.title: Passant
reviews.text: Zeer aangenaam , eten zeer goed en vlot op tafel . Geen gezeur, nergens wordt een probleem over gemaakt . Relaxed, parkeren voor de deur , niets dan lof . 500m van Rotterdam AirPort . Kortom ... fijn dat het ook zo kan , goed eten , betaalbaar , vriendelijke bediening en bestelling snel op tafel. 3e keer hier en altijd een aangename verrassing !
